<p>Hello there, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-szabo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7084461); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7084461&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608136910" alt="Dr Szabo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7084461)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-szabo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7084461); return false;">Dr Szabo</a></span>. Welcome to the SCP Wiki!</p>
<p>Glad to see you're interested in writing for the Wiki. I'm Hexick, and I'm a Junior Staff member on the Community Outreach Team, along with several others. When getting into writing for the site, it's usually a good idea to read around a bit to gauge what the community is interested in. I personally suggest checking out <a href="/scp-5858">SCP-5858</a>. Anyway, here are some resources to help you out around the site as you enter in to your creative endeavor:</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">◎&nbsp;Open&nbsp;Resources&nbsp;◎</a></div>
