<p>Hello hello <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-ivan-hext" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7083622); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7083622&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1607104864" alt="Dr Ivan Hext" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7083622)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-ivan-hext" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7083622); return false;">Dr Ivan Hext</a></span> and welcome to the Wiki! I'm a site author and member of the Community Outreach Team, and this comment is a little info list of resources that will hopefully help you with your journey through the site. We're very happy to see new people excited about writing for the Wiki like you. :)</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>If you're going to try your hand at writing, try out our <a href="http://scp-sandbox-3.wikidot.com/">Sandbox</a>. You can make yourself a page here to store your drafts, which are in-works articles. Using it, you can link the drafts to reviewers to get their opinions on them before posting.</p>
<p>For hashing out concepts, try out the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-and-brainstorming">Ideas and Brainstorming</a> forum. You can run your ideas by experienced members of the community if you need help refining and fleshing out your concept. It's a very helpful little place for when you want to start your writing journey!</p>
<p>If you have a draft ready, make a thread in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-50864/help:drafts-and-critiques">Drafts and Critiques</a> forum. Remember to check the stickied posts in the relevant thread for guidelines on how best to use each forum. You can also try the IRC chat for real-time feedback.</p>
<p>From site usage to writing tips, the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/guide-hub">Guide Hub</a> contains a wealth of resources geared towards helping members produce successful articles. Within the Guides, you will find useful information written by experienced members of the site for the use of newer ones.</p>
<p>The more time you take to familiarize yourself with the SCP style, the drafting process, and the community, the greater your chances are for success! Remember - there is no rush to writing! Take your time! The more time you spend on fleshing your ideas out, the more your chance of success becomes!</p>
<p>As far as reading is concerned, you might want to check out <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/top-rated-pages-this-month">Top Rated New Pages</a>, which will display the most popular recent articles. It's helpful to keep up with what's being received well by the community to implement into your very own writing. Alternatively, you might want to look at the <a href="/user-curated-lists">User Curated Lists</a> page, where members of the community list and rank their favorite articles in different genres and themes, showing which attempts at such are successful and what the community likes.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Best of luck with your future contributions to the site! I hope you enjoy your time here as much as we do! If you have any more questions, feel free to message me here on Wikidot or on the IRC chats!</p>

							</div>

								
